Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 11th May 2025 
Last Updated: 11th May 2025

1. Introduction
Welcome! Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile game, available on the Play Store.

2. Information We Collect
We do not actively collect or store personal user data. The only data processed by our app is gathered through third-party services, including:

In-App Purchases (IAP): Transactions related to in-app purchases are managed through the platform's API (e.g., Google Play). We do not store any financial or personal information.

Ad Services (AdMob): Ads are provided via third-party ad networks that may collect anonymized data for ad personalization and analytics.

3. How We Use Collected Data
The data collected through third-party services is used exclusively for:

Processing in-app purchases securely.

Delivering appropriate advertisements based on user interactions.

Ensuring compliance with child safety regulations (as applicable).

4. Third-Party Services
We use reputable third-party services to manage purchases and ads. These providers may collect and process data in accordance with their own privacy policies. We encourage users to review the privacy policies of:

Google Play IAP Privacy Policy

Google AdMob Privacy Policy

5. Children's Privacy
Our game is suitable for all ages. Advertisements served within the app comply with regulations for children's privacy and are suitable for underage users. We do not knowingly collect any personal data.

6. Data Security
We take appropriate security measures to protect user data handled by third-party services. However, we encourage users to manage their privacy settings within their respective accounts.

7. Your Rights & Choices
Users can:

Disable personalized ads through their Google account settings.
Manage app permissions in their device settings.
Disable mobile connection on order to block ADS.


8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We encourage users to review this document for any changes.

9. Contact Us
For any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: doodlebrainslab@gmail.com
